The Chronicle    Nqobile Tshili STAKEHOLDERS in the education sector have converged at Townsend High School in Bulawayo to address issues to do with gangs and violence in schools. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685084 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-1-16.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-1-16.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-1-16-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The meeting follows the stabbing to death of a Founders High School pupil, Wayne Ndlovu. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685086 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-2-13.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-2-13.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-2-13-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Wayne was killed by a 17-year-old pupil from Hamilton High School in schools related turf war two weeks ago. His killer was arrested and has been charged with murder. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685095 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-5-18.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-5-18.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-5-18-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> In attendance are school heads, teachers, Primary and Secondary Education Ministry officials, pupils, police, church organisations and civil society organisations. <img class="alignnone wp-image-685089 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-3-17.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-3-17.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/02/Untitled-3-17-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The meeting is aimed at finding solutions to address the issue of gang violence and drug abuse in schools.